text.section:
The Authority consists of:
The Secretary of Housing and Community Development;
The Secretary of Business and Economic Development;
The Secretary of Higher Education;
The Secretary of Transportation;
The Secretary of Natural Resources;
The Secretary of the Department of Planning;
The State Historic Preservation Officer; and
Ten members appointed by the Governor with the advice and consent of the Senate:
Two of whom shall be elected officials or representatives of local jurisdictions;
Two of whom shall be appointed from names recommended by the President of the Maryland Senate;
Two of whom shall be appointed from names recommended by the Speaker of the House of Delegates;
One of whom is a public member of the Maryland Greenways Commission;
One of whom is a public member of the Maryland Tourism Development Board;
One of whom is a member of the public who has significant education or experience in historic preservation; and
One of whom is a member of the public who has significant education or experience in heritage tourism.
